
            

            <p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/X7xYp.jpg" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/X7xYp.jpg" alt="enter image description here"></a>I'd like to make current line number in relative line number mode more distinguishable</p>

<pre><code>(setq nlinum-format-function 'myformat)
(defun myformat (line width)
  (if
    (eq line (what-line)) "123  "
    "321"
  )
)
</code></pre>

<p>Notice padding to the right of the current line number in vim which very subtly makes it easily distinguishable.</p>

        